OL,6,F"We get phone calls asking why we're
OL,7,Fnot open because they desperately need
OL,8,Fsomething for their families and
OL,9,Fbecause we're all volunteers it makes
OL,10,Fit fairly difficult."
OL,12,FMs Wakeham says the main reason for
OL,13,Fthe increase in demand is the cost of
OL,14,Fliving.
OL,16,F"Food has become almost inaccessible
OL,17,Fit's so expensive. What used to be a
OL,18,F#50 shop is now a #100 shop. What used
OL,19,Fto feed a family won't last you a week.
