OL,3,C'Food has become almost inaccessible
OL,4,Cit's so expensive'
OL,6,F"It's the same with our family. A #100
OL,7,Fshop used to last us coming up to a
OL,8,Ffortnight, now we're not getting past
OL,9,Fthe week with it."
OL,11,FMs Wakeham receives Universal Credit -
OL,12,Fa scheme set up by the Department for
OL,13,FWork and Pensions (DWP) where a single
OL,14,Fmonthly benefit payment is made for
OL,15,Fworking age people who are on a low
OL,16,Fincome or out of work.
OL,18,FShe says she only manages it because
OL,19,F"we don't go anywhere, we don't go on
OL,20,Fholiday. Everything gets booked in
OL,21,Fadvance.
